social_posts.post_text: Bungou Stray Dogs meets Sanrio! Did you know there was a collaboration of the anime with Sanrio not too long ago? This one is inspired by the Kuromi and Dazai mash up! My client flew in from Sacramento for this one and I really can’t believe how incredible that is. Thank you so much, Rei!
Thank you guys for making this my reality! Words will never be able to express my gratitude
The mightiest Inosuke! Sorry for the bad lighting !!
My books open on January 1st for all projects! I would absolutely love to take on more big pieces like these guys!

My books open on January 1st! At that time, I will be scheduling for February, March and April! I would absolutely love to take on more projects like this one. Character work is my absolute favorite ! Tbh any stupid bright anime tattoos are my favorite to make. Not sure about your idea? Have some questions about my process? Shoot me an email , I’m happy to help! There’s a button on my main for emails , or you can copy pasta : 🍬 libbyloutattoo@gmail.com 🍬
A kitsune Power from my flash for Maddie!

The flashiest boy! Some fresh and some healed on this on this colorful guy! 

(っ◔◡◔)っ ♥ Wanna make an appointment? ♥

✨My books open so soon on January 1st! I will be looking to take on more projects like this one that are colorful and bright! To book with me, just fill out a form through the link in my bio on January 1st. Super simple! I can’t wait to see what you all have in store for me 💕

It’s happening!

✨On January 1st I will be opening my books for the first time in a LONG time! For this round of booking, I will be scheduling the months of February, March and April! I am looking to take on more colorful anime and Kawaii projects! Make ‘em cute, make ‘em lewd, make ‘em action packed pew pew! I wanna do it all. Portraits, chibis, desserts, 90s/y2k nostalgia- bring it at me! I will make all of your magical wishes of bright colorful tattoos come true!

✨To book an appointment with me, please check out my booking info highlight so you have all the basic info you need! Then just complete a booking form and I’ll be in touch as soon as I can! Since the information collected on the form is so crucial to the booking process, I will not be responding to incomplete forms, so please make sure you have your info ready on the 1st! 

✨A non-refundable deposit is required for all appointments and can be made by Zelle or PayPal!

` 🎀  𝐹💗𝓇 𝒶𝓁𝓁 𝒸𝓊𝓇𝓇𝑒𝓃𝓉 𝒸𝓁𝒾𝑒𝓃𝓉𝓈 🎀 `

✨If you have a work in progress , ongoing large scale project or are on the waitlist - you will have early access to booking on December 31st at midnight Arizona time!
I won’t stop talking about it because I am SO EXCITED!!!

My books open on January 1st and I am absolutely dying to do more like this ! Tap the link in my bio to submit your booking inquiry! 🍜 I love food. I love anime portraits. I love drawing both! Let’s make some cute snacks& desserts with your fav character in thrown into the mixing bowl!  Anime food always looks so much more enticing than the real deal, why not decorate your meat suit with it?

.

This one has some fresh and some healed! I feel like this tattoo was a journey and I’m really thankful I got to participate on that quest . I learned a lot from this tattoo and I’m really happy with how it came out! This is definitely one of my faves of 2022. Thank you for trusting me, Brittany! I can’t wait to add more to your collection 💜
I’m starting the new year right and opening my books on January 1st!! Check the link in my bio to fill out a form💕

What an incredible year! 2022 was easily one of the best and worst years of my life, all in one. 2022 was the year that I focused on character work and portraits! It felt like I was an apprentice all over again. I have always wanted to focus on characters, but have never been able to articulate that in my art! I feel like I have so much to learn, but your trust and support has steadily guided me on this wild ride of tattooing! Thank you all so much for being so kind and supporting me! 2023 is truly going to be wonderful and I have so much in store for you guys! Thank you for dedicating your skin to being a bunch of fucking weebs✨

That’s a wrap, you guys! My books are now closed. I am so eternally thankful for those of you that let me carve silly little rainbows into your silly little piles of flesh ! I really love tattooing and you guys are the best part of the whole process 💕

✨If we are currently exchanging messages, you are in the clear!

✨Next round of booking should be closer to March/April!

Giving lil Choi her very own post! This tattoo is one of my favorites that I have ever done and I am so happy it’s apart of Clair’s Clamp themed leg sleeve! Chobits was such a core memory, you TRY and tell me you can listen to that intro without it being stuck in your head for weeeeeeks afterwards.
Who’s pumped for the second season of Tokyo Revengers!?

The Haitani brothers! Tokyo Revengers BUT MAKE IT …egirlxcore! My client, Kaitlin is an actual land angel and made quite the voyage for this tattoo! So proud of her for making it through all that color 💕
Capped off 2022 with this cutie patootie!!
Oh Armin, what are we going to do with you?
My client told me that this was her fun tattoo. Out of all your tattoos , please come to me just for fun

Ya’ll ready for a super sappy caption ? Well here it is! As a kid, I was bullied relentlessly for being overweight. I was about 13 when I hit my highest weight , pushing me into the category of “morbid obesity”. By high school I struggled with losing the weight in a healthy manner, but by my early 20s I did it! I was able to positively transform my own body and lose over 100lbs! Some days I still struggle with healthy eating and taking care of myself , but the sheer feeling of transformation really keeps me going. 

When I started collecting tattoos, that transformation felt even more powerful. In a way I never though was possible! I have always wanted to share that love and light with my clients. I really feel like it’s my true purpose on this silly planet and I’m really thankful for those of you that choose me to create your tattoos!

Kawaii Gaara! This one sits on the back of the arm and scales from elbow to wrist! The lines and background are healed. All other color is fresh! The bottom is super fresh in the photos, since that was finished last - but overall I am so happy with this piece ! I’m really passionate about making big projects like these. They permit so many fun details and color blends! Thank you Brittany for giving me all the cool projects and all the freedom in the world, I’m honored to tattoo you 🙏
The Dark Magician! Not to be confused with Dark Magician Girl >:} Your favorite cone headed card master
This one came out so nicely! Im super thankful for those of you that let me make tattoos like this!

Some fresh and some healed on this Shiro! It’s always incredible to me that you guys find it within to sit through such chaos for color . I really love making tattoos like this and it takes a lot for anyone to sit through a color tattoo - big or small!
Recently I had the opportunity to wrap up this Lucy ! This tattoo brings me sheer joy. My client was so strong!!!
A digital dog after my own heart!
This yami kawaii gal was made with so much love !

Stocking Anarchy! Three - four years ago if you had told me that I would be doing a Panty and Stocking tattoo, my lil bb tatter heart would sing. Tattooing is this really wonderful thing where no matter how big or small, sometimes a tattoo can just really bring you (and hopefully your client) joy! This one was made primarily with colors from @cheeseburgerchampion ‘s Anime Sets from @industryinks !
Can a Beserk tattoo be colorful and Bright? Why yes. Yes it can. Now for the love of fucking war can someone please let me tattoo Griffith? PLEASE

The Bomb Devil! Please excuse the shiny night time photo, tattooing is apparently my forte and photography is not. Who else is jonesing for more Chainsaw Man!?!? My client , Luis apparently is - considering he dedicated a whole limb to the anime!
This was my clients first tattoo, like ever!I Not only was this my clients first tattoo, but he flew in from Northern California for this one! Thank you so much Jakob ✨

My books open on April 1st, so are we doing some anime sleeves or what? We wrapped up this addition to Joe’s sleeve just the other day! The lines are healed and so are the water drops. We’ll be connecting the swellbow soon, poor Joe
Have questions? Send me an email! There’s a button right on my profile 💕

MORE MONSTER GIRLS PLEASE! It took everything in my body not to put this reel to an MSI song from Frankenstein Girls Will Seem Strangely Sexy but I’m like 99% sure none of those songs are ok SO HAVE SOME PLEASANT SOFT INDIE ROCK INSTEAD!

That’s right folks, the time has come! On April 1st at 12am, I will be opening up my books for the summer. As for scheduling, this round will include June, July and August!

As always, I’m looking to take on tons and tons of character work in the form of anime portraits , chibis and keychains! I’m also super ready to get a go on some anime sleeves and do some big , big projects - so please bring them my way!

Booking is super simple, just fill out a form and I’ll send you a text! If you’re more flexible and wanting a spontaneous appointment, I will have a summer waitlist this time around! This summer I will be doing some traveling and a convention, so spots will be a bit limited . I will do my absolute best to get as many of you as possible into my schedule!

My books are opening tonight at midnight ! I am scheduling the months of June, July and August. Fill out a form through the link in my bio and I’ll stab you with all the colorful anime tatties! 

This time around I will be picking ideas based on projects that best fit my style! For this round it will not be first come, first served. I’ll do my best to squeeze as many of you in as possible! Please give me a few days to respond , because you know - im just one person! My books will remain open until my calendar is full. 

Anime portraits both big and small will always be the main game. Keychains with chibis are super cool too! Anime everything is the general consensus. I would really like to work on more male and male presenting characters with darker and more shonen themes to really show you guys what I’ve got! I can tattoo anything I really put my mind to, and let me tell you that shonen tattoos can be bold and bright and colorful!! 

Give a swipe for some characters that I’m dying to tattoo!
Can you imagine?

This is a gender swapped Team Rocket tattoo that I made for my sweet client, Danni! Some is fresh, some is healed💕Sometimes tattooing is surreal. We have filled so much of Danni’s leg that the inner thigh was one of the few spaces we had left! Danni has been coming to me since I was a wee apprentice just about four years ago. That Mimikyu you see to the right is one of the first tattoos I ever did for them! I’m really thankful for clients like Danni, who I can spend hours watching trash reality tv with and sharing little bits of our lives. It’s really a cool thing and I’m very thankful for it 💕

Gudetama x Levi! What an incredible mash up! I was so lucky to make this one for @astroallyart during her guest spot here @uwutattoostudio . It was such a blast to her have in the studio and experience such incredible talent. It’s always an honor to tattoo another tattooer, so thank you Ally for trusting me ! 

.

My books are currently open with select spaces left in July and August! I would love to make more chibi chains like this one! Something about tattooing these keychains is so darn satisfying. It’s a microtrend I’ve grown extremely fond of! Maybe it’s the complexity of the design that’s actually so simple? Maybe it’s that they can literally accommodate any body part or transform into the best gap fillers because they can dangle any which dang way you want em? Maybe it’s the little things like making the clasp into a set of wings for the Wings of Freedom? Tbh maybe they’re just cool to look at!! Well anyway, they make me really happy and I would love to create many more! Fill out a form through the link in my bio and let’s make your own✨
Nico Robin!! Made with so much love @uwutattoostudio! This one is a bit swelly as it sits on the inner arm, but I’m still super happy with how she came out! Now who’s gonna get Nami!?
My books are currently open and you know, I could probably tattoo Chopper a thousand times and still be happy. I’d love to do more One Piece tattoos!

Does anyone else feel like shaking ink bottles is the best way to get gassed up for a tattoo? Selecting ink is so powerful. Shaking it is the uproar to the pour. And then? Then comes the symphony of physically tattooing. This craft is a true gift from the universe and so was this tattoo! I have wanted this tattoo for my own body for a long time! To create it for another truly made me feel like a magical girl. Madoka is my all time favorite anime. Ever. To tattoo Madoka in this particular form was really , really cool
null

All hail Maddie, the coolest client that never lets me down! I subconsciously manifested this tattoo in a previous session with her and had no idea until I was half way through this very tattoo. Evidently I had told her I really wanted to tattoo Killua and his yoyos 🪀 (Did you know there’s a yo-yo emoji?!!) Last week Maddie saved the day by filling a last minute availability that I had and voila! Cinna is just the perfect companion for a kid like Killua, I don’t make the rules
The Immortal Dragon has accepted his wildest of missions. As…the maid !!!! No one’s ever going to understand how excited I was to mix the perfect blue black for his tattoos.

I mean I just really can’t phantom, I mean, fathom why Machi would be wearing a clown outfit!! 🕷️ This tattoo was made for one of the coolest clients ever and im really thankful to add to her collection!
null

Sometimes you have big plans and sometimes the body has other plans! Just like it says, this one was big ouchies so we will be finishing the color once it’s healed ✨ And there’s absolutely nothing wrong with that! This one is a little wrappy around the back of the calf, but I’m so happy with how things are coming out! Thank you Andy 💕

The Dark Magician Girl!!! This tattoo has such a wild back story! Basically, my clients husband had me tattoo the Dark Magician on him a few months ago. At his session, my client Anna and I were just chatting and she had mentioned the concept of getting the Dark Magician Girl tattooed on herself! Essentially this is the weeb-iest couples tattoo ever!

Gon Freecs!! I’m always so happy to do HunterXHunter tattoos! This lil Gon is a bit smaller than hand sized and tbh it was sooo nice to do a tiny tat for once. I LOVE making big pieces, but I think every artist likes to mix things up and keep things shakin. It was cool to use tiny needles and simplify my color blends. Thank you SO much to Thomas and Morgan for getting both Gon AND Killua (I’ll be posting him l8r) as matching but not matching tattoos! And thank you guys for indulging in one of my favorite shows, love on the spectrum with me!!!
This lil Killua is the other half to the matching tattoos from my post earlier today
It was really fun to make this Draculaura in my style but VERY HARD to narrow down her accessories and outfit. She’s such an icon, everything she does is just so0o0o cool!!!
Healed Blair! Soul Eater is absolutely one of my favorite animes in the entire world

A sweet lil bubblepop Rebecca from my flash for Maddie’s leg sleeve! Lines are healed and color is fresh on this one. This one wraps around the back of the thigh and Maddie was a pure warrior for that placement alone!  Choom

Yuji and Nobara based on a manga panel that my client sent in! Please never be afraid to ask for anything at all, like a manga panel. I can do almost anything in my style! If you can share a handful of trust, I can supply a whole limbs worth of colorful scabs! Thank you to Nick for trusting me with your first color tattoo, you did incredible!!!
I LOVE CHIBI TATS!! Love a character but don’t want a whole ass portrait? Get a lil Chibi!!
Cat boy Pain, what a sight to see. What song do you think he would sing you at the maid cafe? Probably one of scorn and hate .
I was so happy to make this Rei x Kazuki shipped in this colorbomb! Thank you so much Bree , for watching true crime docuseries and chatting about art with me!

True or false : once you hear this song, you can’t I hear it for at least five days? I always loved the soundtracks to the Persona games! I was so happy when @carls_inks asked me for this Joker tattoo! You all need to check out her art asap , she makes such solid,  cute designs💕
I’m so so happy that I got to tattoo this dumb dog. This Denjichan was from my flash! It was made with so much love @uwutattoostudio 💕

Miku x Gumi chibi chain! The linework in this one is healed and color is fresh. Aaand the tattoos above it were done by me about three or so years ago during my apprenticeship! It’s wild to have clients that I’ve known over the years, you guys are like family to me and I’m so thankful for that 💕

Truth be told, I would absolutely kill to do more Bleach tattoos! This summer has been full of so many good tattoos and I am so thankful for those of you that bare through these long days for these big projects. This was my clients first big color tattoo and she did so so amazing through the whole thing!! This tattoo was also my first time trying any type of mag from @emalla.official and it’s safe to say that I am soooo in love with their needles!
Yumeko ! Have you seen Kalegurui? I can’t believe it’s almost been a year since Twin was released. The color palettes of this anime are so mesmerizing, I love it a lot
Erza Scarlett! Who else loves Fairy Tail *this* much?

Come see me and my shop @uwutattoostudio at the very first @gilatattooexpo ! I’m fully booked for the weekend, but would love to meet all of you! If you’re not there, you’re so square - so get your tickets now!!

Inosuke is definitely one of my favorite (hes one in my heart for any sticklers out there)! Who’s yours?!

If you wanna see me make more like this lil piggy, stop by the @gilatattooexpo this weekend!! I’ve got some cool stuff planned for the show 😎
I’m really stoked to have the opportunity to work on such cool projects! I’m super appreciative of anyone who comes to my chair for such cool ideas!

I don’t think I’ve ever been happier to make a tattoo for @dornoh - who is in fact, a big ass man. (Someone even stopped at our booth to assure us of that!) I really can’t speak highly enough of @gilatattooexpo and @tattoosbydondon for how fun this show was! My friends and clients really showed up for this one to enter for the contests / to get tattooed and it was cool! @dornoh missed a whole ass show with his band, @spicymayobitch just to get this very tattoo! @claireltier came postop from freaking surgery on her leg and got tattooed at the show. @poppy.pettals came all the way from Portland just to enter her Jojos tattoo that I did last year! And @youmadbro_orjustmaddie was super brave to get on stage and show off her leg sleeve that we’ve been working on. It was really special to have so many of my favorite people in one place. This was such a fun experience and i can’t wait for next year!

Okay gamers , it’s that time again !! My books are opening back up on August 27th! Here’s the scoop:

🌸 My books will open right at midnight on August 27th ! I will be scheduling out the rest of the year. This means appointments will be scheduled for the months October, November and December!

🌸 Booking is super simple! Just fill out a form through the link in my bio and I’ll send you a text . Easy peasy! 

🌸A $200 deposit is required to schedule in! If you have any questions, please feel free to review my deposit form through the very same link in my bio.  It is always up for your reference and review. Please hold off on filling out any deposit forms until you are scheduled in! 

🌸I am currently looking to take on more anime portraits that are bright and colorful! Kawaii is always in the cards, but anime is my central focus at this time. My style is a bright take on 90’s / 00’s anime and I can make virtually any character in my style! Video games are always welcome💕

🌸Having trouble thinking of your idea? Check my Flash highlight for pre drawn tattoos! To book a flash design, just screenshot the design you’d like and upload it to your form. All flash is priced by the piece and based on all the variables of the tattoo you desire! (Size, placement , etc )

🌸 If you have a work in progess, now’s your time to shine! This means that if you have an unfinished tattoo, this will be your last opportunity to book for 2023. I would love to see your beautiful faces and get your projects all wrapped up! 

🌸I will leave my books open for a few days up to a week to give everyone a chance to get their bookings in! Right up to and during this period I am going to be screaming it from the mountain tops that my books are open. Don’t miss it!

Really, if you need a new anime tattoo - I know a girl! It’s me! Hi! I’m the problem, it’s me.

👏 Vash and Wolf 👏 This ones for Roger, who drove all the way up from way Southern Arizona just for the multiple sessions of this tattoo. Sometimes tattooing brings you to meet the coolest of people and Roger is definitely one of them! Roger and his wife are really wonderful people! Roger streams all sorts of neat stuff, check him out @mydude_az

GEEEENYA!!! This was done in two sessions and my client made the grand voyage for Tucson for both of them ! I really can’t express how much it means that you guys travel for your tattoos. That’s just bananas ! But anyway, I’m really happy with how this Genya turned out. Let me know what you think!
Tattoos like this are why I love tattooing!! More like this, please!
I present to you, the Kuromi Tomie! My client Jackie was so kind to let me really go crazy with this one and it was really nice to just like, let my brain do the thing. Thank you so much Jackie!
It was an absolute honor to make this memorial tattoo! Thank you for trusting me, Celeste! I’ve still never been brave enough to watch Your Lie in April..,
Todoroki loves cats! This one was done in one shot for my incredibly tough client, Mandy! I’m really in love with out this turned out. It was fun to tattoo it too!!

I could write a book about this honestly, but it’s been incredible to see this industry evolve. I hope to grow with it! I want to tattoo till my hands actually  fall off. And when they do? I’ll make ink! Tattooing has given me a life I could never dream of and I will work hard eternally to make sure I return the favor to this industry. Here’s to three years from now, when my tattoos will be even bigger and even better!
Hi, it’s me - your local supplier of bunny girl tats

@gilatattooexpo  is she gonna win two years in a row ???? We will see!

You read it right, folks! My books are officially open for my holiday waitlist! Here’s how it works:

🌸It’s the most wonderful time of year, but not always for us scab masters ! The holiday waitlist gives ya’ll exclusive access and first dibs on last minute openings throughout the holiday season! 

🌸To get your cutie patootie on that waitlist , just fill out a form through the link in my bio. It’s easy peasy!

🌸The following slides are projects I am looking to prioritize based on my own silly little special interests. They include Bee and Puppy, Fiona and Cake, any of the MikuxPokemon collabs and Toiletbound! These are by no means limitations of concepts, but I’ll definitely give hefty priority to any of those babies 😉

🌸Responses will be sent out starting on the third and could take up to a week to get back to everyone! Please be patient 💕

🌸Last but not least, thank you endlessly for your support ! I really love tattooing and every day that I get to do it is a gift . You guys keep me so dang busy and I will never not appreciate that!

I freaking love tattooing!!! So much so that I don’t want to ever think about NOT doing it. If you have an ounce of compassion in your heart, please let me tattoo this holiday season and get on my freaking waitlist!!!

Nelliel , the girl, the gal , the one and only! This Jose’s second tattoo of Nel, and probably won’t be his last . As a tattooer, sometimes you have tattoos that you reeeeally look forward to. Pretty much all month I was dreaming of this tattoo! It is always an honor to tattoo anyone’s hand, so thank you Jose!!

This tattoo was made with @crybabytattooproducts , @industryinks and so much love!

Big projects are something I’ve dreamed of doing since I was a wee lil apprenti ! I still dream of doing even bigger projects. I live for tattoos like these where we chip away to get as much color as possible 🌈  One day I really hope to be filling limbs and backs and tummies and just bodies in general with BIG , large scale work on a regular basis! 

Every single one of these tattoos was made with so much love and the perfect brew of  @crybabytattooproducts and @industryinks
Strawberry milk Mitsuri!

Well now you know! I’m so in love with this one! I really, really have an affinity to Nintendo right now, so bring me all of your princess portraits! This tattoo was made with @emalla.official cartridges and they are seriously the best!
I freaking love Joe’s sleeve! Tbh I wish my arms looked like this

We are so excited to announce @libbyloutattoo  will be doing a ANIME SEMINAR! 2024 @gilatattooexpo  you are not going to want to miss out! DETAILS COMING SOON!

Nurse Boy! I’m back in my Pokémon era you guys!!! And tbh I’m kinda sad this tattoo is over! I had a lot of fun making little hair clips and picking which Pokémon to add to the design based on the variety my client proposed . My client was nothing short of a genius to request this gender swapped Nurse Joy and I am sooo happy with how this one came out!
I really can’t express how excited I am about this one !
The time hath comets! And my books are , after all, open … 👀

The holiday season is upon us and there’s no better time than to TREAT 👏 YOUR 👏 SELF 👏! I’m discounting all of these designs by $600 for anyone that books them before November 5th! Please fill out a form through the link in my bio to get your give one of these puppies a forever home✨

Genyaaaaa! Recently I realized that I often make reels of my tattoos and never make a good ole fashion, rootin tootin post about them! So here we are! I’m dying to do more Demon Slayer. I really am! Let’s make that happen.
Piccolo! You want kawaii Dragonball? I got chu!

Mash ups are some of my favorite tattoos. Why not have your cake and eat it too? For this one, my client Noelle requested that we have the My Hero Gang as each of the original Powerpuff Girls!! Tbh I had a LOT of fun with this one and I’m always down for more mashups !

Iykyk 😉 all tattoos are different and some require multiple sessions! It’s easy to breeze by thousands of tattoos every day in your feed , but it’s good to know that some of them weren’t done in one sit and that’s okay!

Blossom, Bubbles and Buttercup! As a keychain. But it’s the My Hero boys. As chibis? Noelle served up this idea and I about screamed. I still love the keychain microtrend and I sure love everything about this one!
